{
  "texts": [
    "Normalisation applies weights to the token counts with diminishing importance for tokens that occur in the majority of documents.",
    "This produces a floating-point vector x 2 R V.",
    "A common approach is the so-called \"TF-IDF\" transform.",
    "It multiplies the term frequency (TF) x obtained from the bag-of-words by the \"inverse document-frequency\" (IDF), which is a function of the inverse of the proportion of documents which contain the term, with some additional normalisation.",
    "For more details we refer to Baeza-Yates & Ribeiro-Neto (2011) and Manning et al. (2008)."
  ]
}